b'' b'' b" <reference to running ati's install program and using" b' its functions to position/size images at various' b' resolutions' b'' b'i thought this was a neat feature until i noticed that' b'when an image is re-sized, the scanning frequency is' b'necessarily changed. this causes digital multiscan' b'monitors like my mag mx17f to get confused as to which' b'mode to use if the frequency gets too far from the' b'standard selections. for this reason, i use the' b'"factory defaults" for position/size on the ati card' b'and adjust each mode individually (only the first time)' b'at the monitor. the mag (and many other multiscan' b'monitors) has (have) the ability to recall these settings' b'the next time each mode is "detected".' b'--' b'' b'=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=' b'' 